criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. fluid collections within two weeks of disease onset;

          2. single- or multi-organ failure;

          3. CTSI > = 7 (initial CT performed within 7 days after the onset of disease.); and (4)
             acute physiology and chronic health evaluation (APACHE) II score > = 8.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. patients without APD interventions;

          2. patients who underwent necrosectomy directly after APD without PCD as a bridge
             therapy;

          3. previous percutaneous drainage or surgical necrosectomy during the episode of
             pancreatitis;

          4. previous exploratory laparotomy for acute abdomen and intraoperative diagnosis of AP.
